The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 06 November is 96,368 (11,107 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 01 November, there were 4,847 new confirmed cases (558.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 October, there were 4,597 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 5% (250 extra cases).
